The reason why clones are important for us comes from the following fact: if A is omega-categorical (and in particular if A is a reduct of a homogeneous structure), then the coclone defined by A can be characterized as the set of all relations that are invariant by all polymorphisms of A. For finite A, this fact discovered in the sixties and generalised later by Bodirsky and Nesetril to omega-categorical structures. }
