9}{\cf1\afs28\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs28\loch\f5
 The way complexity is encoded into clones is through the natural notion of homomorphism between clones. A map between two clones is called a homomorphism if it commutes with composition with projections. The definition immediately implies that homomorphisms preserve flat equations: for example, the image of a binary commutative operation has to be commutative, for commutativity can be stated as a \u8220\'93flat\u8221\'94 statement. Under this homomorphism preorder, there is a minimal element, namely the clone of projections on the set \{0,1\}. The clone of projections corresponds to the clone of polymorphism of the classical boolean satisfiability problem, which is NP-complete.}
