11}{\cf1\afs28\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs28\loch\f5
 This result also motivates the following question. Recall that if the canonical subclone has no homomorphism to the projections, then the CSP is polynomial-time tractable, and that if the full clone has a homomorphism to the projections, then the CSP is NP-hard. We therefore come naturally to the following problem: can every homomorphism from the canonical subclone to the projections be extended to a homomorphism from the full clone to the projections? Note that if true, then this is enough to prove the Bodirsky-Pinsker conjecture.}
